                <head>148. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On July 28 the Yugoslav Government informed the United States that it accepted
                    the proposed U.S. text of the military aid termination note. The Yugoslav
                    Government had previously (October 23, 1958) accepted the U.S. proposed text of
                    a note concluding an agreement for the purchase of military equipment. The two
                    agreements came into effect simultaneously through an exchange of notes in
                    Belgrade on August 25, 1959. For text of the agreement terminating military aid,
                    see 10 <gloss target="#t_UST1">UST</gloss> 1468. For text of the agreement
                    relating to the purchase of military supplies, materials, and services, see 10
                        <gloss target="#t_UST1">UST</gloss> 1474.</p>
            </div>
